cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.LO, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with cooperative manipulation of a single object by robotic agents, and proposes a distributed control protocol for trajectory tracking. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper involves multiple agents working together to achieve a common goal, and uses load sharing coefficients to represent differences in power capabilities among the agents. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a hybrid control algorithm for the satisfaction of a given temporal logic formula, and deals with the control of a coupled object-agents system. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper employs standard automata-based methodologies to derive a control algorithm for the satisfaction of a temporal logic formula. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): While not the main focus of the paper, the proposed control algorithm could potentially be implemented using programming languages and tools for distributed systems.
